The paper deals with the topic of adversarial examples in image classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the transferability of these attacks to different neural network architectures, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the security of these attacks, which falls under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of these attacks in the real world, which is a topic of interest in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
